    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-19T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="779"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/9–1445:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Political Adviser for Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-19T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 19, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>508. Dept considers that it would be desirable to request information of Russians
                    on details of projected land redistribution, including anticipated effect on
                    agricultural output and possible contribution to resettlement of German refugees
                    from the East. In making this inquiry we should avoid conveying impression that
                    we are opposed to land reform or even that we feel its execution should be
                    delayed. <pb facs="1064" n="1054" xml:id="pg_1054"/> (Reurtel 521, September 14,
                    5 pm<note n="66" xml:id="d779fn66">Not printed, but see footnote 65, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>). It should be pointed out that JCS
                        1067/6<note n="67" xml:id="d779fn67">Not printed, but see paragraph 28 of
                        the final revision of JCS 1067 (IPCOG 1), pp. 484, 495.</note> directs
                    utilization of large landed assets to facilitate accommodation and settlement of
                    Germans and others or to increase agricultural output. Dept is of view that
                    application of uniform land reform measures throughout Germany would be highly
                    desirable and that an effort might well be made in Control Council to negotiate
                    uniform policies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
